content:
Store Screen Pop Instructions in a Variable

If you add multiple Add Screen Pop actions to a flow, define a collection variable to aggregate and store all screen pop instructions. This way, you don't have to worry about the order in which the Add Screen Pop actions are added to the flow.

Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with the Service Cloud

Define a variable to store the Add Screen Pop action's instructions.
Create a variable under Resource Type > Variable in the Manager tab of Toolbox.
Set Data Type to Record and select Allow multiple values (collection).
Select Pending Service Routing Interaction Information as the Object.

Use the variable to store the first Add Screen Pop action's output, and use it as input and output for all subsequent Add Screen Pop actions in the flow.

Edit the Add Screen Pop action and set its input variables from the collection variable.
Expand Advanced and manually assign variables to write the results of the Add Screen Pop action to the variable.
Pass the screen pop instructions from the variable to the Route Work action by selecting it under Set Additional Input Values.
Save the flow.
title: Configuring Service Cloud Routing with Variables
